description.narrative: UNICEF increased efforts in building capacity of policymakers to develop and implement policies and services for adolescent mental health and child injury prevention. Health Management Information Systems (HMIS) were strengthened across 76,981 health facilities. A public advocacy campaign on adolescent mental health was combined with the release of UNICEF’s flagship State of The World’s Children’s Report 2021.
